Explanation:

The solution uses a Map to store the key-value pairs and a boolean variable to keep track of the last accessed time. When a key is accessed, the last accessed time is updated, and when a key is updated, the least frequently used key is evicted. The time complexity is O(1) for both get and put operations, as we only perform constant operations on the data structure. The space complexity is O(n), where n is the number of elements in the cache, as we store n key-value pairs in the Map. The energy implications are low, as the algorithm only uses a few operations and does not consume significant energy.

